cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper proposes an approach to predict the 3D shape and pose of objects in a scene by incorporating relationships amongst them. This involves reasoning about pairwise relations in the form of relative 3D pose. Given that the paper deals with computer vision and robotics, cs.CV and cs.RO are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves learning-based methods, which suggests cs.LG as another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves reasoning and prediction, which suggests cs.AI as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with 3D prediction, which suggests cs.GR as a possible sub-category.
